WEBVTT

00:01.540 --> 00:03.580
♪♪

00:03.580 --> 00:06.040
[ Snorting ]

00:06.040 --> 00:08.750
Katie: Ooh!
Looks like Santa forgot one.

00:08.750 --> 00:10.830
[ Gasps ] Presents!

00:10.830 --> 00:12.790
[ Chuckles ]

00:12.790 --> 00:15.960
Merry Christmas,
sweetheart.

00:15.960 --> 00:18.000
You look handsome
in your new outfit.

00:18.000 --> 00:19.920
Really? 'Cause I risked it this
year and went full mannequin.

00:19.920 --> 00:22.540
Whatever the mannequin
was wearing, I bought.

00:22.540 --> 00:24.790
Everybody freeze!
You know the drill.

00:24.790 --> 00:27.710
First we build a fire,
then we have a big breakfast,

00:27.710 --> 00:30.170
then Dad gives his "True Meaning
of Christmas" speech, then...

00:30.170 --> 00:31.620
Oliver cuts me off
and says...

00:31.620 --> 00:32.750
Can we just get
to the presents?

00:32.750 --> 00:33.880
And then you say...

00:33.880 --> 00:35.420
Don't make me hit you
on Christmas.

00:35.420 --> 00:37.790
And then I finish the speech,
and we all open presents.

00:37.790 --> 00:40.460
And that's
our family tradition.

00:40.460 --> 00:42.580
All we need is Dad's seasonal
hypochondria to kick in.

00:42.580 --> 00:43.580
Ha, ha.

00:43.580 --> 00:45.290
It's not hypochondria
if it's real.

00:45.290 --> 00:46.920
My hands
are definitely tingling.

00:46.920 --> 00:48.080
It feels like carpal tunnel

00:48.080 --> 00:49.580
from wrapping all those presents
last night.

00:49.580 --> 00:51.540
Or maybe it's arthritis.
My nanna had hands like this.

00:51.540 --> 00:54.790
It's not arthritis.
Taylor's right.

00:54.790 --> 00:57.380
Your hypochondria flares up
every Christmas

00:57.380 --> 00:59.460
because you know all
the doctors' offices are closed.

00:59.460 --> 01:00.960
There's always Dr. Weber
down the street.

01:00.960 --> 01:02.120
He retired
and moved to Oregon.

01:02.120 --> 01:03.790
He just
euthanizes people now.

01:03.790 --> 01:05.920
Let's just get through
these stupid traditions...

01:07.500 --> 01:09.000
...that are so meaningful.

01:09.000 --> 01:14.920
♪♪

01:14.920 --> 01:21.080
♪♪

01:21.080 --> 01:22.620
The crackle of the fireplace,

01:22.620 --> 01:24.460
the smell of apples
and cinnamon,

01:24.460 --> 01:27.580
snow on the windowsill are all
what make Christmas special.

01:27.580 --> 01:29.330
But -- But the people
in this room --

01:29.330 --> 01:30.620
that's what makes Christmas
the most special of all.

01:30.620 --> 01:31.880
Presents!

01:33.580 --> 01:36.290
I hope Santa brought me
volume two of "The Big Finish:

01:36.290 --> 01:38.790
Rich, Famous,
and How They Died."

01:38.790 --> 01:40.880
I practically memorized
volume one.

01:40.880 --> 01:42.210
Attila the Hun got drunk

01:42.210 --> 01:44.210
and died of a nosebleed
on his wedding night.

01:44.210 --> 01:47.040
He drowned
in his own blood.

01:47.040 --> 01:48.960
[ Scoffs ]
Attila...

01:48.960 --> 01:50.540
Where are my
ballet tickets?

01:50.540 --> 01:53.960
Envelope or are they just trying
to trick me with the big box?

01:53.960 --> 01:55.830
I hope love is in one
of these packages,

01:55.830 --> 01:58.500
because I don't have any
since Eyo and I broke up.

01:58.500 --> 02:00.170
I hope a muzzle is in one
of those packages.

02:00.170 --> 02:04.000
[ Telephone rings ]

02:04.000 --> 02:05.710
What's making
that noise?

02:05.710 --> 02:07.830
It sounds familiar.

02:07.830 --> 02:09.120
It's the landline!

02:09.120 --> 02:10.290
No one calls the landline
unless --

02:10.290 --> 02:11.580
Somebody's dead.

02:11.580 --> 02:13.170
Or it's that computer
that tries to trick you

02:13.170 --> 02:14.620
into thinking
it's a real person.

02:14.620 --> 02:15.750
"Hi, this is Amy.

02:15.750 --> 02:17.330
Give me a moment
to adjust my headset."

02:17.330 --> 02:18.710
She gets me every time.

02:18.710 --> 02:20.250
[ Ringing stops ]
Nobody move!

02:20.250 --> 02:23.210
The tradition is,
we open presents together.

02:23.210 --> 02:24.460
[ All groan ]

02:24.460 --> 02:26.040
Hello?

02:26.040 --> 02:28.000
Drugs!
Give me drugs, you hack!

02:28.000 --> 02:29.710
Doris?
Oh, finally.

02:29.710 --> 02:30.750
Katie, where are you?!

02:30.750 --> 02:32.620
I've been texting you
like crazy!

02:32.620 --> 02:33.960
I didn't get any --

02:33.960 --> 02:35.710
Oh.

02:35.710 --> 02:37.790
I'm in labor,
and I'm all alone!

02:37.790 --> 02:39.330
Where's your family?

02:39.330 --> 02:41.380
Aspen. I wasn't due
for another two weeks,

02:41.380 --> 02:43.830
so I sent everybody out of town
because I'm huge,

02:43.830 --> 02:46.290
and my body's producing a gas
that made our dog run away.

02:46.290 --> 02:47.710
Okay, well,
what do you want me to do?

02:47.710 --> 02:49.210
Get your butt over here.

02:49.210 --> 02:51.420
I'm not giving birth alone
like some teenage crack whore.

02:51.420 --> 02:52.620
I'll be right there.
We just need to open --

02:52.620 --> 02:53.830
Now!

02:53.830 --> 02:56.040
Okay, I'm coming.

02:56.040 --> 02:58.540
Doris is having
a baby.

02:58.540 --> 03:02.080
Nobody touches anything.
Christmas is on hold.

03:02.080 --> 03:03.460
[ All groan ]

03:03.460 --> 03:04.750
Don't worry.
It's her fourth.

03:04.750 --> 03:06.460
Hopefully,
it'll slide right out.

03:12.080 --> 03:14.750
Mom, you can't go anywhere.
We have to open our presents.

03:14.750 --> 03:16.580
No!
Not until I get back.

03:16.580 --> 03:18.000
This is madness!

03:18.000 --> 03:19.040
Do my hands look blue to you?

03:19.040 --> 03:20.460
You're perfectly fine.

03:20.460 --> 03:22.170
And under no circumstances
are you to try

03:22.170 --> 03:23.420
to diagnose yourself
online.

03:23.420 --> 03:24.460
You know what happens.

03:24.460 --> 03:26.330
♪♪

03:26.330 --> 03:28.120
Do my eyes look yellow
to you?

03:28.120 --> 03:29.670
I feel like my liver
isn't working.

03:31.080 --> 03:33.960
My poop is floating.

03:33.960 --> 03:35.420
I'm pretty sure my pancreas
is shutting down.

03:35.420 --> 03:36.670
Take a look.

03:38.210 --> 03:39.540
I smell burnt toast,

03:39.540 --> 03:40.540
so I think I'm having a stroke.

03:40.540 --> 03:41.920
That's regular toast.

03:41.920 --> 03:43.120
I'm smelling stroke toast.

03:44.920 --> 03:46.330
I hear you,

03:46.330 --> 03:47.250
but let me Google my symptoms
just once.

03:47.250 --> 03:48.250
I'll even take Bing.

03:48.250 --> 03:49.830
Let me Bing my symptoms.

03:49.830 --> 03:51.380
No Internet.
I'll be back as soon as I can.

03:51.380 --> 03:52.460
And no matter what,

03:52.460 --> 03:54.330
do not let them open
their presents.

03:54.330 --> 03:59.420
♪♪

03:59.420 --> 04:04.830
♪♪

04:04.830 --> 04:06.960
I can't believe you have to lock
our presents up in your office

04:06.960 --> 04:08.500
because you don't
trust us.

04:08.500 --> 04:09.620
Is that where we're at,
Dad?

04:14.710 --> 04:16.250
That's where I'm at.

04:16.250 --> 04:17.500
I just want to make sure
that's where you were at, too.

04:17.500 --> 04:20.250
Out. Out. Out!

04:22.040 --> 04:24.210
No presents.
No boyfriend.

04:24.210 --> 04:25.290
[ Sighs ]

04:25.290 --> 04:27.750
Being single on the holidays
is so hard.

04:27.750 --> 04:29.670
Some problems Santa
can't even fix.

04:29.670 --> 04:32.920
Reel it in, Adele.
I've got my own stuff.

04:32.920 --> 04:34.210
I need to know
if I got those tickets

04:34.210 --> 04:36.580
to "The Nutcracker."
Why?

04:36.580 --> 04:38.830
So you can take that girl
from your ballet class?

04:38.830 --> 04:39.920
Yes.

04:39.920 --> 04:41.960
Ooh, you like her?

04:41.960 --> 04:44.540
I think I do.
Knock it off.

04:44.540 --> 04:46.000
How am I supposed to tease you
when you're acting this way?

04:47.170 --> 04:48.330
Have you asked her yet?

04:48.330 --> 04:51.620
[ Classical music plays ]

04:51.620 --> 04:52.580
So, I was wondering --

04:52.580 --> 04:53.790
What?

04:53.790 --> 04:57.830
♪♪

04:57.830 --> 04:59.000
I've got no game.

04:59.000 --> 05:00.500
It's just so frustrating

05:00.500 --> 05:02.000
because I'm agile,

05:02.000 --> 05:04.830
I'm smart,
the face is working.

05:04.830 --> 05:05.710
Let me help you.

05:05.710 --> 05:07.380
Why would you do that?

05:07.380 --> 05:09.120
Because I have no love
this Christmas,

05:09.120 --> 05:11.330
but maybe with my guidance,
you can.

05:11.330 --> 05:13.420
Pretend I'm Gina.
Ask me out.

05:13.420 --> 05:16.120
Go sell "Flowers in the Attic"
someplace else.

05:16.120 --> 05:17.750
I'm just gonna tape the ticket
to her door

05:17.750 --> 05:19.330
and hope she shows up
to the performance.

05:19.330 --> 05:20.710
But first,
I need the tickets.

05:20.710 --> 05:22.040
I have an idea.

05:22.040 --> 05:24.120
We take a cobra,
put it under the door,

05:24.120 --> 05:27.380
Dad comes running out,
we go in and get the presents.

05:27.380 --> 05:28.750
Where are you
gonna get a cobra?

05:28.750 --> 05:30.960
I asked Santa for one,
and...

05:30.960 --> 05:32.880
Wait a second.

05:32.880 --> 05:34.540
That's not gonna work.

05:34.540 --> 05:37.080
The cobra's in one of the
presents in Dad's office.

05:37.080 --> 05:38.710
I feel stupid.

05:38.710 --> 05:43.750
♪♪

05:43.750 --> 05:49.000
♪♪

05:49.000 --> 05:50.330
This...

05:50.330 --> 05:51.790
is a hospital room?

05:51.790 --> 05:53.040
The deluxe suite.

05:53.040 --> 05:55.040
News flash --
rich people live better.

05:55.040 --> 05:56.670
Doris, my family's
waiting on me.

05:56.670 --> 05:58.000
When are Richard and the kids
getting here?

05:58.000 --> 05:59.670
Ugh.
Their flight's delayed.

05:59.670 --> 06:01.580
Angela's texting with him
for updates.

06:01.580 --> 06:03.460
Angela: Hi, Katie.

06:03.460 --> 06:05.210
Angela?

06:05.210 --> 06:07.330
Hi! How's Vermont?

06:07.330 --> 06:08.750
Well, it really would be great

06:08.750 --> 06:10.580
if I wasn't spending it
with my ex

06:10.580 --> 06:12.750
and her parents
who were already mad at me

06:12.750 --> 06:14.040
for "turning her gay."

06:14.040 --> 06:15.330
[ Scoffs ]
When I met her,

06:15.330 --> 06:17.120
she owned a pit bull named
Tracy Chapman --

06:17.120 --> 06:19.380
The seeds were planted.
I just watered them.

06:19.380 --> 06:21.580
Well, at least this Christmas
is gonna be exciting

06:21.580 --> 06:23.920
because Doris is
having a baby.

06:23.920 --> 06:26.710
No, I am not.
No Christmas baby.

06:26.710 --> 06:28.670
Christmas is my favorite day
out of the year,

06:28.670 --> 06:30.540
and I'm not gonna let this thing
spoil it.

06:30.540 --> 06:33.040
I ruin my kids' lives.
They don't ruin mine!

06:34.460 --> 06:36.540
I'm keeping this thing in
until midnight.

06:36.540 --> 06:38.460
Uh, if it's not healthy
to hold in your pee,

06:38.460 --> 06:40.290
I can't imagine it's healthy
to hold in a baby.

06:40.290 --> 06:42.380
[ Scoffs ]
[ Ringtone plays ]

06:44.620 --> 06:45.880
[ Groans ]

06:45.880 --> 06:49.290
Hey, honey.
I'm gonna be here for a while.

06:49.290 --> 06:51.040
[ Pounding on door ] No, no. You
need to come home right now.

06:51.040 --> 06:52.670
The kids are
driving me crazy.

06:52.670 --> 06:55.830
I can't come home yet.
Doris' family is delayed.

06:55.830 --> 06:57.290
What's that noise?

06:57.290 --> 06:58.830
Our children demanding
their presents.

06:58.830 --> 07:01.580
Taylor: Dad! Anna-Kat fell down,
and she's bleeding!

07:01.580 --> 07:03.170
You need to come
out here now!

07:06.290 --> 07:08.170
Slide something under the door
with her blood on it.

07:10.210 --> 07:12.460
Anna-Kat:
Open the damn door, Greg!

07:12.460 --> 07:14.420
I'm seeing a very upsetting side
of our children.

07:14.420 --> 07:16.170
I'm gonna let them open the presents.
No way.

07:16.170 --> 07:19.250
The family tradition is that
we open presents together --

07:19.250 --> 07:21.920
breakfast, fireplace,
speech, presents.

07:21.920 --> 07:24.250
That's really your tradition
that you grew up with.

07:24.250 --> 07:26.420
Maybe our new tradition
should be more "casual fun"

07:26.420 --> 07:27.880
and less "desperate
hostage situation."

07:27.880 --> 07:30.040
No. A desperate
hostage situation

07:30.040 --> 07:31.540
is what Christmas
is all about.

07:31.540 --> 07:34.330
Why do you think "Die Hard"
is a stone-cold classic?

07:34.330 --> 07:36.620
Well, what am I supposed to do if we can't
open our gifts until we're all together?

07:36.620 --> 07:38.960
Figure it out!

07:38.960 --> 07:39.750
[ Pounding continues ]

07:39.750 --> 07:46.620
♪♪

07:46.620 --> 07:48.460
Oh, look at all
those presents.

07:48.460 --> 07:49.830
The pediatric ward
is this way.

07:49.830 --> 07:52.120
Oh. No.

07:52.120 --> 07:53.380
These are for us.

07:54.790 --> 07:56.210
[ Quietly ] Let's go.

07:59.080 --> 08:02.210
[ Meditation music plays ]

08:06.830 --> 08:08.120
[ Music stops ]

08:08.120 --> 08:10.080
Doris,
if poor people found out

08:10.080 --> 08:11.580
that this is how
the 1% give birth,

08:11.580 --> 08:13.670
they would drown you
in your own cucumber water.

08:13.670 --> 08:14.790
You may be right,

08:14.790 --> 08:16.460
but one of the benefits
of being in the 1%

08:16.460 --> 08:18.330
is we don't care.

08:18.330 --> 08:19.500
[ Footsteps approaching ]

08:19.500 --> 08:21.750
-Whoa.
-Hi, Mama.

08:21.750 --> 08:23.460
What are you guys
doing here?

08:23.460 --> 08:25.670
You told me to figure it out,
so here we are,

08:25.670 --> 08:28.170
all together,
Christmas tradition intact.

08:28.170 --> 08:29.420
Greg, this is not
the tradition.

08:29.420 --> 08:31.250
The tradition is,
we open our presents

08:31.250 --> 08:32.710
in front of the fireplace.

08:32.710 --> 08:33.790
There's a fireplace.

08:33.790 --> 08:35.380
What? Where?

08:35.380 --> 08:38.170
In the parlor. Taylor.

08:38.170 --> 08:39.380
♪♪

08:39.380 --> 08:40.960
Whoa.

08:43.210 --> 08:44.330
[ Sighs ]

08:46.170 --> 08:48.580
I like the way
ya live, lady.

08:48.580 --> 08:51.080
♪♪

08:55.170 --> 08:56.830
Okay.
It's Christmas.

08:56.830 --> 08:57.960
And we're all together.

08:57.960 --> 08:59.880
And there's a fireplace.

08:59.880 --> 09:01.750
Check, check, check.

09:01.750 --> 09:02.790
But we don't have
breakfast.

09:04.290 --> 09:05.920
You can just order
room service.

09:05.920 --> 09:08.290
We're not having hospital food
for Christmas breakfast.

09:08.290 --> 09:10.920
A nice breakfast --
that's our tradition.

09:10.920 --> 09:12.620
Nurse, what are
the specials?

09:12.620 --> 09:15.120
Today, we have caviar
on homemade blinis

09:15.120 --> 09:16.330
with a dollop
of crÃ¨me fraÃ®che

09:16.330 --> 09:18.920
or poached wild salmon
with hollandaise

09:18.920 --> 09:20.500
and ricotta avocado
crostini cups.

09:20.500 --> 09:23.420
Enough.
Who wants to eat that slop?

09:23.420 --> 09:26.380
All right, Mom.
Now you're just making excuses.

09:26.380 --> 09:28.880
This is the nicest Christmas
we've ever had.

09:28.880 --> 09:30.330
It's a nicer room.

09:30.330 --> 09:32.040
It's better food.

09:32.040 --> 09:33.210
We have our own
waitress.

09:33.210 --> 09:35.330
Oh, I'm not a waitress.
I'm a nurse.

09:35.330 --> 09:36.790
[ Scoffs ] Okay.

09:36.790 --> 09:38.420
Oh! You're a nurse.
Could you look at my hands?

09:38.420 --> 09:39.670
I think they're
getting bluer.

09:39.670 --> 09:40.880
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

09:40.880 --> 09:42.580
Okay, I'm gonna need everyone
to step out now.

09:42.580 --> 09:44.380
You heard her.
Everyone out.

09:44.380 --> 09:45.250
Your presents are
gonna have to wait.

09:45.250 --> 09:47.210
And, Greg,
your hands are fine.

09:47.210 --> 09:49.580
Doris has an actual
medical emergency.

09:50.830 --> 09:52.960
Hey, is something wrong?
What's that thing beeping for?

09:52.960 --> 09:54.420
Everything's okay.

09:54.420 --> 09:56.170
Someone just unplugged
your fetal monitor

09:56.170 --> 09:57.750
and the backup battery
ran low.

09:57.750 --> 09:59.880
Oh. Sorry, my bad.

09:59.880 --> 10:01.250
I was gonna charge
my phone.

10:01.250 --> 10:03.670
♪♪

10:03.670 --> 10:04.960
Maybe Mom's right.

10:04.960 --> 10:06.380
Maybe I'm just
making myself crazy.

10:06.380 --> 10:08.710
Al Capone thought
he was going crazy,

10:08.710 --> 10:11.750
but in reality,
it was the syphilitic dementia.

10:11.750 --> 10:12.880
[ Elevator bell dings ]

10:12.880 --> 10:14.330
You know, if you want
to ask Gina out,

10:14.330 --> 10:16.330
you should practice first
by asking someone else out.

10:16.330 --> 10:17.500
Who?

10:17.500 --> 10:19.250
Anyone.

10:19.250 --> 10:20.710
How about her?

10:20.710 --> 10:22.120
Are you nuts?

10:22.120 --> 10:23.540
She's like 80.

10:23.540 --> 10:25.460
It's not like
she's gonna go out with you.

10:25.460 --> 10:27.040
It's just practice
getting the words out.

10:27.040 --> 10:30.120
Just go up there, be charming,
make her laugh.

10:30.120 --> 10:32.750
Eyo and I used to laugh
all the time.

10:32.750 --> 10:34.330
Maybe we were meant
to be together,

10:34.330 --> 10:36.000
and I just threw it
all away.

10:36.000 --> 10:37.750
Maybe he's my soul mate,
and I --

10:37.750 --> 10:39.170
All right. All right.
You win.

10:39.170 --> 10:40.670
I can't listen to this.

10:40.670 --> 10:42.620
I'm gonna take a run
at the granny in the gift shop.

10:44.540 --> 10:52.750
♪♪

10:52.750 --> 10:56.420
Hi. Um...

10:56.420 --> 10:58.960
If you don't have
anything to do,

10:58.960 --> 11:02.330
would you like to...

11:02.330 --> 11:04.080
sell me this license-plate
key chain?

11:04.080 --> 11:06.670
Sure...

11:06.670 --> 11:07.830
Larry.

11:09.210 --> 11:10.540
So?

11:10.540 --> 11:11.960
Great advice.

11:11.960 --> 11:14.330
My confidence
is officially in the toilet.

11:14.330 --> 11:17.920
And I just spent like $8
on a license-plate key chain.

11:17.920 --> 11:20.290
Eyo's car had
a license plate.

11:20.290 --> 11:23.290
Hey,
there's Andrew Wages.

11:23.290 --> 11:25.960
We do Revolutionary War
reenactments together.

11:27.330 --> 11:30.040
I'm gonna go say hi.

11:30.040 --> 11:31.790
Hey, Andrew.
Merry Christmas.

11:31.790 --> 11:33.420
Oh. Hey, Greg.

11:33.420 --> 11:35.000
Bummer you have to work
on Christmas.

11:35.000 --> 11:37.040
Ah, now you think
I'm a terrible doctor.

11:37.040 --> 11:38.620
Well, I'm not.

11:38.620 --> 11:41.540
I just refuse to play
their political games!

11:41.540 --> 11:43.120
[ Sighs ]

11:43.120 --> 11:44.330
Hey, what's going on
with your hands?

11:44.330 --> 11:45.330
Right?

11:45.330 --> 11:46.460
Yeah.
They're bluish gray.

11:46.460 --> 11:47.670
That's what
I've been saying!

11:47.670 --> 11:49.290
You know,
that could be serious.

11:49.290 --> 11:50.920
I knew it could
be serious!

11:50.920 --> 11:52.790
Wait.
It could be serious?

11:52.790 --> 11:55.000
[ Both exhaling slowly ]

11:55.000 --> 11:57.170
It's all right.
Just breathe.

11:57.170 --> 11:58.580
You're having
another contraction.

11:58.580 --> 12:01.790
It's not just the contractions.
I'm having a fourth child.

12:01.790 --> 12:03.580
I told this thing not
to come out until tomorrow,

12:03.580 --> 12:05.540
and the son of a bitch
is already not listening to me.

12:05.540 --> 12:07.670
Uh, do you realize
in that scenario,

12:07.670 --> 12:08.880
you just called yourself
a bitch?

12:08.880 --> 12:10.330
Shut up, laptop.

12:10.330 --> 12:12.420
What am I doing having
another child?

12:12.420 --> 12:14.080
I haven't done a very good job
with my first three.

12:14.080 --> 12:15.670
You have done a great job.

12:15.670 --> 12:16.880
My kids hate me.

12:16.880 --> 12:18.620
That's true.
I take back what I just said.

12:18.620 --> 12:20.580
It's 'cause you tiger-mom
the hell out of them.

12:20.580 --> 12:22.380
Think of baby number four
as an opportunity

12:22.380 --> 12:23.710
to do things differently.

12:23.710 --> 12:26.420
You mean I could, like...
validate its feelings,

12:26.420 --> 12:27.790
even if they're stupid?

12:27.790 --> 12:29.460
Yes.
That's pretty much the job.

12:30.830 --> 12:33.330
We wanted to see
if Doris was okay.

12:33.330 --> 12:34.710
You guys are so sweet.

12:34.710 --> 12:38.290
Yes, she and the baby
are perfectly fine.

12:38.290 --> 12:39.880
Presents!

12:42.250 --> 12:44.080
Okay.

12:44.080 --> 12:45.880
We got the breakfast.

12:45.880 --> 12:47.710
We got the fireplace.

12:47.710 --> 12:49.960
We're all together,
so we can open some --

12:49.960 --> 12:51.580
Hang on.
I don't see your dad.

12:51.580 --> 12:54.120
Oh, Dr. Wages took him
for some blood tests.

12:54.120 --> 12:55.920
What?
That's not possible.

12:55.920 --> 12:58.250
He would've texted me.

12:58.250 --> 12:59.620
Oh.

12:59.620 --> 13:03.120
♪♪

13:03.120 --> 13:04.210
Frankly, I can't believe

13:04.210 --> 13:05.580
you ignored your symptoms
for so long.

13:05.580 --> 13:07.120
[ Sighs ]

13:07.120 --> 13:08.500
Katie, don't
blame yourself,

13:08.500 --> 13:10.250
although that would be the
natural place for you to go.

13:10.250 --> 13:12.580
What do you think it is,
Dr. Wages?

13:12.580 --> 13:13.960
Well, I can't be certain,

13:13.960 --> 13:16.580
but some of the symptoms
are consistent with gangrene.

13:16.580 --> 13:17.750
Are you serious?

13:17.750 --> 13:19.040
Deadly.

13:19.040 --> 13:21.290
It's deadly?
Oh. No. No, sorry.

13:21.290 --> 13:23.420
I just mean I'm really,
really serious.

13:23.420 --> 13:24.710
You're not the first one
to be confused.

13:24.710 --> 13:26.710
Really got to stop doing that.
Mm-hmm.

13:26.710 --> 13:28.620
Amputation is
a far greater risk.

13:28.620 --> 13:30.670
I concur.

13:32.120 --> 13:34.290
My last Christmas
with hands.

13:34.290 --> 13:36.960
♪♪

13:40.830 --> 13:42.120
Look on the bright side --

13:42.120 --> 13:43.500
maybe you'll get hooks
for hands.

13:43.500 --> 13:45.120
That'd be cool.

13:45.120 --> 13:47.080
Plus my friend, Dahlia,
might finally shut up

13:47.080 --> 13:48.960
about her dad's
glass eye.

13:50.620 --> 13:53.000
[ Hushed ] I don't want to have
hooks for hands.

13:53.000 --> 13:55.620
Why don't you guys go wait
with Anna-Kat in the hall?

13:57.710 --> 14:01.580
Sweetheart, stay calm.
You are not losing anything.

14:01.580 --> 14:03.210
Your friend Doris says
she needs you right away.

14:03.210 --> 14:04.960
Don't worry.

14:04.960 --> 14:06.920
I'm gonna go explain the situation
to Doris and be right back.

14:06.920 --> 14:09.120
But you won't be alone.

14:09.120 --> 14:10.960
Hold on to Angela.

14:10.960 --> 14:12.210
Maybe for the last time.

14:13.290 --> 14:15.250
Hurry back, Katie.

14:16.420 --> 14:18.380
[ Sighs ]
Is Dad gonna be okay?

14:18.380 --> 14:20.080
We're still waiting
on the tests,

14:20.080 --> 14:21.620
but I don't want you guys
to worry.

14:21.620 --> 14:23.380
Yeah, but if they have
to take the hands,

14:23.380 --> 14:24.830
could they replace them
with, like,

14:24.830 --> 14:26.170
Go-Go-Gadget Hands?

14:27.540 --> 14:30.120
Like a whisk
and an umbrella

14:30.120 --> 14:32.250
so he can make pancakes
in the rain.

14:32.250 --> 14:34.420
That's an excellent
silver lining.

14:34.420 --> 14:35.960
I'll be right back.

14:37.750 --> 14:39.040
Poor Dad.

14:39.040 --> 14:41.080
Life can change
in an instant.

14:41.080 --> 14:42.580
I don't want to live
with regrets.

14:42.580 --> 14:44.210
Me neither.

14:44.210 --> 14:46.670
I'm gonna call Eyo
and get back together.

14:46.670 --> 14:50.080
And I'm gonna go ask out
that for-sure-plays-ukulele lady

14:50.080 --> 14:51.250
who works
in the gift shop.

14:51.250 --> 14:52.540
♪♪

14:52.540 --> 14:54.580
You seem better.

14:54.580 --> 14:56.210
Did your drugs kick in?

14:56.210 --> 14:57.290
Totally.

14:57.290 --> 15:00.250
And now I see things
so much clearer.

15:00.250 --> 15:03.540
So I may have made a few
mistakes with my first three.

15:03.540 --> 15:05.420
I'm gonna do better
with this one.

15:05.420 --> 15:07.460
I'm taking a do-over.

15:07.460 --> 15:09.080
That's great, Doris.

15:09.080 --> 15:12.880
Now it's time to unclench
and let nature take its course.

15:12.880 --> 15:15.420
You're right.
I love my Christmas baby.

15:15.420 --> 15:17.080
And I love these drugs.

15:17.080 --> 15:18.460
I'm glad
you're in a good place,

15:18.460 --> 15:20.380
because I've been
neglecting my family,

15:20.380 --> 15:21.540
and I need to get back to Greg.
[ Taps Doris' leg ]

15:21.540 --> 15:23.380
Oh, no. No, no.
Katie, don't go.

15:23.380 --> 15:25.790
Suck some of this stuff
out of my I.V.

15:25.790 --> 15:27.210
and come on this ride
with me.

15:27.210 --> 15:29.000
Got to go.
Next baby!

15:29.000 --> 15:35.620
♪♪

15:35.620 --> 15:38.080
Hi. I'm back.

15:38.080 --> 15:39.920
Seeing as it's Christmas
and all,

15:39.920 --> 15:42.120
I'd like to know
if you'd...

15:45.790 --> 15:47.080
...sell me
this key chain.

15:48.670 --> 15:50.540
That'll be $8...

15:50.540 --> 15:51.830
Jerome.

16:00.330 --> 16:03.460
[ "Dance of the Sugar Plum
Fairy" plays ]

16:08.380 --> 16:09.500
[ Music stops ]

16:11.330 --> 16:14.120
Would you like to see
"The Nutcracker" tomorrow night?

16:14.120 --> 16:17.120
I have two tickets.

16:17.120 --> 16:18.920
I'd love to see "The
Nutcracker." Yes!

16:18.920 --> 16:21.830
My mom died this year,
and my sister and I

16:21.830 --> 16:23.710
used to go see "The Nutcracker"
with her every Christmas.

16:23.710 --> 16:24.790
Oh, wait.
The thing is --

16:24.790 --> 16:26.170
We weren't planning to go
this year,

16:26.170 --> 16:28.750
but then you come in with
two free tickets. No.

16:28.750 --> 16:29.750
You don't understand.

16:29.750 --> 16:31.290
It was my sister's idea
to ask you.

16:31.290 --> 16:33.080
[ Voice breaking ]
Then you're both angels.

16:33.080 --> 16:34.880
It's like my mom sent you
to me --

16:34.880 --> 16:37.290
two little
Christmas angels.

16:38.790 --> 16:40.750
Maybe I won't turn back to drugs
after all.

16:40.750 --> 16:42.000
I got to go.

16:42.000 --> 16:43.830
♪♪

16:43.830 --> 16:46.250
Ooh!
I'm gonna Google your symptoms.

16:46.250 --> 16:47.710
Katie said no checking
the Internet.

16:47.710 --> 16:50.500
She said it to you, not to me.
[ Scoffs ]

16:50.500 --> 16:52.380
There's a whole chat room
of people

16:52.380 --> 16:54.210
whose hands turned blue.

16:54.210 --> 16:56.420
Ooh, you got to love
the Internet.

16:56.420 --> 16:58.000
You know, the other day
my zipper got stuck,

16:58.000 --> 16:59.380
and I couldn't figure out
how to get it loose.

16:59.380 --> 17:02.080
Turns out, you can use
a crayon, Greg.

17:02.080 --> 17:03.960
A crayon!
[ Chuckles ]

17:03.960 --> 17:07.120
Mm.
But you might lose your hands.

17:07.120 --> 17:07.920
[ Glass clinks ]
Let's focus on that.

17:07.920 --> 17:11.120
♪♪

17:11.120 --> 17:12.460
How'd it go?

17:12.460 --> 17:13.790
In the following order,
I think it went

17:13.790 --> 17:17.500
awkward, thrilling,
strange, sad,

17:17.500 --> 17:18.920
and then
purely uncomfortable.

17:18.920 --> 17:20.290
But you asked her out?

17:20.290 --> 17:23.380
Hmm. Yeah.
I guess I did.

17:23.380 --> 17:24.580
You call Eyo?

17:24.580 --> 17:26.830
Yep, and as soon
as I heard his voice,

17:26.830 --> 17:28.830
I realized breaking up
was the right decision,

17:28.830 --> 17:30.210
and I'm standing by it.

17:30.210 --> 17:32.210
Also, he's dating
Bruce Westfield,

17:32.210 --> 17:33.710
the co-captain
of the water polo team,

17:33.710 --> 17:35.460
so that helped.

17:35.460 --> 17:37.210
♪♪

17:37.210 --> 17:38.830
Did you buy any new pants
recently?

17:38.830 --> 17:42.170
I bought some jeans,
back when framing my thighs

17:42.170 --> 17:43.750
seemed like
such an important thing.

17:43.750 --> 17:45.250
No. Listen.

17:45.250 --> 17:47.210
Find some rubbing alcohol
and rub it on your hands.

17:47.210 --> 17:50.290
I don't think alcohol
is...

17:50.290 --> 17:51.170
gonna...

17:54.580 --> 17:55.830
Oh, my God.

17:55.830 --> 17:57.250
The blue is coming off!

17:57.250 --> 17:59.040
It's your new pants!
It's a thing.

17:59.040 --> 18:00.330
There's a guy that
figured out

18:00.330 --> 18:01.710
he was rubbing his hands
on his new jeans,

18:01.710 --> 18:03.080
and the blue dye
was coming off.

18:03.080 --> 18:04.580
Look at that.

18:04.580 --> 18:06.330
My hands were tingling
from the carpal tunnel.

18:06.330 --> 18:07.830
I must have rubbed them
on my pants --

18:07.830 --> 18:09.710
Oh, no. Katie's gonna think
I'm an idiot.

18:09.710 --> 18:11.170
At least you're not
gonna lose your hands.

18:11.170 --> 18:12.420
[ Laughs ]

18:12.420 --> 18:14.330
How are you doing?

18:14.330 --> 18:15.540
There's something
you should know.

18:15.540 --> 18:17.330
No, there's something
you should know.

18:17.330 --> 18:19.710
I am sorry that
I didn't listen to you

18:19.710 --> 18:21.210
when you said
something was wrong.

18:21.210 --> 18:23.580
I-It's okay, Katie.
You should know that I-I --

18:23.580 --> 18:26.670
No. You were suffering,
and I just brushed it off.

18:26.670 --> 18:29.380
I'm gonna change, Greg.

18:29.380 --> 18:30.960
I'm gonna be better.

18:30.960 --> 18:32.330
From now on,

18:32.330 --> 18:34.750
I'm gonna be the wife
that you need me to be.

18:34.750 --> 18:36.380
Katie...

18:38.790 --> 18:39.960
...that sounds great.

18:39.960 --> 18:41.540
Uh, aren't you
gonna tell her --

18:41.540 --> 18:43.670
I'm sure with your unconditional
love and support,

18:43.670 --> 18:45.210
this thing will just go away
on its own.

18:45.210 --> 18:46.670
I should have been there
for you,

18:46.670 --> 18:48.460
but I was more focused
on Doris

18:48.460 --> 18:50.210
and my stupid
Christmas traditions.

18:50.210 --> 18:51.460
It's not stupid.

18:51.460 --> 18:52.960
Annoying, certainly.

18:52.960 --> 18:55.080
Inflexible, yes.

18:55.080 --> 18:56.620
It's just what we used to do
when I was a kid.

18:56.620 --> 18:59.380
Growing up, my mom always
traveled for work,

18:59.380 --> 19:02.000
but the only time that we could
depend on her to be home

19:02.000 --> 19:04.170
was on Christmas Day.

19:04.170 --> 19:07.830
That's why these traditions
are so important to me.

19:07.830 --> 19:10.000
Sweetie, we don't need traditions
to keep our family together.

19:10.000 --> 19:11.500
We're always together.

19:11.500 --> 19:13.790
I'm not going anywhere.
The kids aren't going anywhere.

19:13.790 --> 19:15.920
And my hands...

19:15.920 --> 19:17.250
aren't going anywhere.

19:17.250 --> 19:18.830
What?

19:18.830 --> 19:21.080
It was my pants.

19:21.080 --> 19:22.540
I [Sighs]
My carpal tunnel

19:22.540 --> 19:24.620
was making me rub my hands
on my new jeans,

19:24.620 --> 19:27.420
and the dye turned
my hands blue, so...

19:27.420 --> 19:28.710
Wait.

19:28.710 --> 19:30.960
So, you're okay?
It was nothing?

19:30.960 --> 19:34.210
I know what you're thinking --
It's a Christmas miracle.

19:35.670 --> 19:38.040
[ Chuckles ]

19:38.040 --> 19:42.000
[ Doris screams in distance ]

19:42.000 --> 19:42.960
Go take care
of your friend.

19:47.620 --> 19:50.670
Don't you ever flip me down
again, Greg.

19:50.670 --> 19:54.250
♪♪

19:54.250 --> 19:56.920
Who's Mommy's do-over baby?
You are.

19:56.920 --> 19:58.710
I'm gonna spoil you,

19:58.710 --> 20:01.120
and it's gonna drive a wedge
between you and your siblings.

20:01.120 --> 20:03.380
Yes, it will.

20:03.380 --> 20:05.670
Thanks for being there
for me.

20:05.670 --> 20:07.500
Now go find your family.

20:07.500 --> 20:08.790
Nah.

20:08.790 --> 20:10.710
I already sent them home
to open presents.

20:10.710 --> 20:13.380
I was driving
everyone crazy.

20:13.380 --> 20:15.290
You should learn to be
a good mom like me.

20:17.460 --> 20:18.960
Merry Christmas!

20:18.960 --> 20:24.880
♪♪

20:24.880 --> 20:26.250
Go for it.

20:26.250 --> 20:27.620
Presents!

20:27.620 --> 20:30.080
♪♪

20:34.620 --> 20:36.120
I hope you and your sister
have a nice time.

20:39.080 --> 20:41.330
Thank you...

20:41.330 --> 20:42.290
Larry Jerome.

20:43.670 --> 20:48.790
[ Classical music plays ]

20:48.790 --> 20:50.170
So, I was wondering...

20:50.170 --> 20:51.750
What?

20:51.750 --> 20:54.210
Would you like to go out
some time?

20:54.210 --> 20:56.120
Where?

20:56.120 --> 20:57.420
I don't know.

20:57.420 --> 20:59.620
Okay.

20:59.620 --> 21:02.210
♪♪
